# 09.05 Stage 3 — Execution OS

## Overview

Stage 3 defines the transformation of cmdOS from an AI Agent Platform into a complete AI Execution Operating System.

At this stage, cmdOS moves beyond creating and managing AI Agents.

The system gains the ability to execute tasks across real digital environments, including:

- Desktop systems
- Mobile devices
- Applications
- Cloud services
- Enterprise platforms

The core objective is to enable AI Agents to perform real-world computer operations.

Core principle:

AI Agent Platform

↓

Execution Layer

↓

Digital Environment Control

↓

Real-World Task Completion

---

# 1. Stage 3 Purpose

The purpose of Stage 3 is to build the execution capabilities required for cmdOS to operate as an AI-native operating system.

Main objectives:

- Enable cross-application execution
- Build Desktop Agent
- Build Mobile Agent
- Create universal execution capabilities
- Support complex autonomous workflows

---

# 2. Stage 3 Position

Stage 3 follows the creation of the Agent Platform.

Roadmap relationship:

Stage 0

↓

Stage 1 MVP

↓

Stage 2 Agent Platform

↓

